-- D. Outside The Box Questions
-- The following are open ended questions which might be asked during a technical interview for this case study - there are no right or wrong answers, 
-- but answers that make sense from both a technical and a business perspective make an amazing impression!

-- 1. How would you calculate the rate of growth for Foodie-Fi?
-- With the data that we have, by using the compounded monthly growth rate (CMGR), which measures monthly growth on an investment over a certain periot of time.
-- The formula is (sum of latest month's payment/sum of first month's payment)*(1/ number of months) - 1

-- 2. What key metrics would you recommend Foodie-Fi management to track over time to assess performance of their overall business?
-- ● Conversion rate
-- ● Customer acquisition cost
-- ● Customer lifetime value
-- ● Customer retention rate
-- ● New and paying customer to churning customers ratio
-- ● Total watch time and amount of videos watched
-- ● Gross profit margin
-- ● EBITDA
-- ● Number of subscribers

-- 3. What are some key customer journeys or experiences that you would analyse further to improve customer retention?
-- ● Make signing up to the platform simple and painless
-- ● Offer something to retain the customer when they ask to cancel the plan (like an upgrade for X months or extend the plan for X motnhs for free, in case they have an annual plan)
-- ● Provide content for all age groups
-- ● Provide new content often
-- ● Make the search engine intuitive and meaningful so it's easier to discover new content, work on the categories
-- ● Perform extensive research on the user interface's usability and UX/UI design to eliminate any barriers and improve user experience
-- ● Refine the suggestions' algorithm

-- 4. If the Foodie-Fi team were to create an exit survey shown to customers who wish to cancel their subscription, what questions would you include in the survey?
-- ● Why have you decided to cancel your subscription?
-- ● What did you like about Foodie-Fi?
-- ● How could we improve?
-- ● How likely are you to return?
-- ● Will you still be interested to know about our new products/services in the future?
-- ● Anything else you would like to share?

-- 5. What business levers could the Foodie-Fi team use to reduce the customer churn rate? How would you validate the effectiveness of your ideas?


